message.content: $16\ge \lvert2x + 7\rvert$ means that $-16 \le 2x+7 \le 16$. Subtracting 7 gives  \[-23\le 2x\le 9.\] Dividing by 2 gives \[-\frac{23}{2} \le x\le \frac{9}{2}.\] Therefore, the possible integer values of $x$ are $-11$, $-10, \ldots, 4$ inclusive. The least integer value is $\boxed{-11}$.
